      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DISTINCTION (1) is a well performed dog and winner of 15 races who was in the minor money last time out at Bendigo (23.93). Hard to go past form here at this journey. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Well placed and gets her chance. REPELLENT (4) has a strong record this track and trip including two wins from three starts. Comes off a (25.19) win last time, scoring by 1.3 lengths in a R/A FIN over 450m at Ballarat. Can feature with the right run. OBSCURUS (2) finished well back at Sandown last time when a 10 length fifth (30.15) but back to the course now of his latest success. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Worth following up. MINER MICK (5) was strongly fancied but finished third last time (28.06) at Bendigo, bringing a two-run winning streak to an end. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card.",
